sus that post-9/11 drama primarily engages with ‘the real’, Ariane de Waal argues that these plays navigate the complexities of the discourse – rather than the historical or social realities – of war and terrorism. British ‘theatre on terror’ negotiates, inflects, and participates in the discursive circulation of stories, idioms, controversies, testimonies, and pieces of (mis)information in the face of global insecurities.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aBritisches Gegenwartstheater. 4aElfter September. 4aTerror. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Drama.2bisacsh  a9/11.  aContemporary British Theatre.  aDrama.  aSubject Positions.  aTerror.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831105154350 cprintz978311051512140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311051708840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110517088423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110517088/original  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-076249-5  DG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5E